::Prowl::

Prowl frowns as he feels Iron Raptor nearly fall under him, managing 
to stay on her. He slides off as she comes to a stop, setting Iris on 
the ground, concerned about whether Iron Raptor's leg was allright.

"Are you allright, love?" he asks, putting a hand on her, behind her 
shoulder, and looking at it in concern.



--- In nbwrpg@egroups.com, "Megan Solmonson" <tmrattrap@h...> wrote:
> 
> 
> * Iron Raptors shoulder jerked but absoebed the impact the best way 
it knew 
> how as her front limb came down hard onto a rock which slipped out 
from

> Almost falling she decides to slow down to a small jog, wondering 
if they 
> were closer to the area which Iris had selected for this merge she 
kept

> She heard the programs annoyed yip.*
>

>

about

> 
> * And with that she simply turned back around, taking what comfort 
she could 
> at the feeling of Prowl relaxing on her back as he was.

small herds 
> of grass grazing animals off in the distance, slightly wondering if 
this was 
> the right place in which Iris wanted to stop.
> And her question was comfirmed.*
> 
> IRIS:" Stop! We're here. You ready, Birdman?"
> 
> * Iron Raptor came to a stop and rolled her shoulder in its socket, 
grinding 
> her teeth at the aching pain she felt in the joint.
> She shook herself hard, even though Prowl was still on her back 
holding 
> Iris.
> She just didn't like the feeling of someone on her back.
> How horses stood it during the time of humans was completely beyond 
her.*
> 
> " Is it a good idea to do this with both of us injured? Couldn't it 
cause 
> problems?"
